			  			Q: When trying to set a defense plan I just get a 'white screen' or 'grey box'.<br />
A: This is problem with your java plug-in version. First, make sure you have the latest Java plug-in from Java.com.<br />
If that doesn't work then in Internet Explorer, go to Tools-&gt;Internet Options...-&gt;Advanced<br />
Make sure Java (Sun)-&gt;Use Java 2 v1.x.x for &lt;applet&gt; is checked.<br />
Make sure all boxes under Microsoft JVM are checked<br />
<br />
i can set out my ships in the defense plan, but when i submit the plan i get a file not found 404<br />
<br />
i don't have a category called Microsoft JVM at all, so when i try to view battle reports all i get is the grey box and red X<br />
<br />
i have windows XP serivce pack 2 and java 2 platform standard edition 1.4.2_05<br />
<br />
i know this probably isn't a bug, but this board is the closest to tech support, so hopefully someone can help me.<br />
